How do you specify multiple GPUS when starting the image generator from command line? `pm2 start run.sh --name wombo-image-generator --interpreter bash`

Or via `run_docker.sh` ?
vtrust is still low for a lot of validators so I suspect that it might be because not enough are setting weights atm
the image generator can't use multiple GPUs, it can only generate with one at a time. you can however run multiple image generators against different GPUs and use a load balanced generation endpoint

like ashley said its for 1 gpu. so essentially you'll just start like 8 of them if its an 8x machine, heres an example for 4, note that I dont use the run.sh but you can!:
```
CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 PORT=11699 pm2 start venv/bin/python --name "miner_endpoint" -- -m image_generator.main --name wombo-image-generator --interpreter bash

CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=1 PORT=11700 pm2 start venv/bin/python --name "miner_endpoint2" -- -m image_generator.main --name wombo-image-generator --interpreter bash

CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=2 PORT=11702 pm2 start venv/bin/python --name "miner_endpoint3" -- -m image_generator.main --name wombo-image-generator --interpreter bash

CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=3 PORT=11703 pm2 start venv/bin/python --name "miner_endpoint4" -- -m image_generator.main --name wombo-image-generator --interpreter bash
```

these set the env for that instance for CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES to select the gpu cuda will use in that instance, and PORT to specify the port that the image generation endpoint will listen on, you dont have to inline it, theres pm2 ecosystems and stuff too but yeah

@deleted-role apologies for the continued pings, but we have pushed more updates!
This one mostly concerns validators, we have pushed several updates that work to achieve the following(in order of importance):
- *Removing the Validator API, both the locally hosted and freely available one hosted by WOMBO*
  - This means that running a validator will now always require a GPU. The minimum requirements have been updated with the recommended compute.
  - This should hopefully reduce the number of errors when our hosted API is on a different version than the validator, or when it is under load.
- Added a safety check to block bad/inappropriate requests
- Improved UID selection and made user request penalties slightly harsher
Please update at your earliest convenience, if not running an auto-update script, *additionally, we will rework our auto-update scripts at some point soon to make them better suited for the general use cases, for both miners and validators*
also, as always, please report any issues you may find!

Tying it to generation speed (as most big miners will be able to achieve 256) just aligns us to other image generation subnets as well (23 for instance)

there's also not much to tweak in terms of generation speed between miners, it depends on the gpu more than anything. when it becomes more important to generate faster, people will try to abuse this somehow, but I suppose they could be doing that now anyways.

there's also a few ways I can think of to increase generation speed but have poorer true RPS. the other downside I can think of is GPU diversity will suffer as the fastest ones are identified, it becomes less important to build a capable network, more important to just get 32 a100s/h100s (can prob do 256 with 32 of them, maybe less).
